The vote on revenue sharing, due on Monday, has been postponed a record eight times over disagreements on a contentious formula for distributing 316.5bn Kenyan shillings ($2.9bn) among 47 counties. Former Majority Leader Kipchumba Murkomen told the senate on Monday that Senators Cleophas Malala, Christopher Langat were arrested at their homes in the capital, Nairobi, while Ltumbesi Lelegwe was arrested on his way to the senate. The police have yet to respond to the claims. The senators on Monday called for an adjournment of proceedings to debate the alleged arrest of their colleagues: --BBC--